{%- comment -%}
  Marks a rendered value as click-to-editable in the Editor's preview.

  Usage:
    <h2 {% render 'classic/snippets/editable', field: 'heading', value: section.heading %}>
      {{ heading }}
    </h2>

  It emits the STORED value, not the rendered one, and that distinction is the
  whole point.

  Every heading renders through `| default: 'Support a Cause'`, so a section with
  no stored heading still SHOWS one. If the Editor read the rendered text back out
  of the DOM, then merely clicking into a heading and clicking away would save
  "Support a Cause" as if the merchant had typed it: the default would be baked in
  permanently and the fallback would be dead. The merchant would have no way to get
  it back.

  So the element carries data-mcloud-stored="" for an unset field, and the Editor
  diffs against THAT, never against textContent. Blank means blank.

  Inert outside the preview: nothing styles or scripts these attributes on the
  public site.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- comment -%}
  Emits NOTHING outside the editor: these attributes carry the merchant's stored
  copy, and a visitor has no business receiving it.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if editing -%}data-mcloud-field="{{ field }}" data-mcloud-stored="{{ value | escape }}"{%- endif -%}
